《地铁莎蒂》由阿尔弗雷德·桑特尔执导<ref name="NBOR" />，阿黛尔·科曼迪尼和保罗·斯科菲尔德把米尔德里德·克拉姆（{{lang|en|Mildred Cram}}）于1925年发表在《[[红皮书|红皮书杂志]]》（{{lang|en|''The Red Book Magazine''}}）上的短篇故事《沙漠莎蒂》（{{lang|en|''Sadie of the Desert''}}）改编成本片的剧本<ref name="afi">{{cite web | title = Subway Sadie | url = http://www.afi.com/members/catalog/DetailView.aspx?s=1&Movie=12478 | archivedate = 2014-04-17 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140417023013/http://www.afi.com/members/catalog/DetailView.aspx?s=1&Movie=12478 | deadurl = no | work = [[美国影艺协会|American Film Institute]] | accessdate = 2014-08-06 }}</ref>。

电影于1926年5月3日开始进入制作阶段<ref>{{cite web | title = Peggy Shaw in Subway Sadie | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131105200955/http://www.archive.org/stream/filmdaily3536newy#page/1248/mode/2up | url = http://archive.org/stream/filmdaily3536newy#page/1248/mode/2up | website = The Film Daily | publisher = [[互联网档案馆|Internet Archive]] | archivedate = 2013-11-05}}</ref>。艾尔·罗克特是影片的[[制片人|制片人]]和制片主任，他与桑特尔一起选择了电影中的演员。杰克·马尔霍尔获选饰演男主角赫伯·麦卡锡。虽然已经坐过很多次地铁，但他从没注意到其中的警卫，所以为了演好这个角色，他坐了“几乎整整一天”的地铁，来对这些警卫加以观察<ref>{{cite news | title = Jack Mulhall Rides Subway for Accuracy | url = http://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=2194&dat=19261016&id=AcUuAAAAIBAJ&sjid=o9kFAAAAIBAJ&pg=5532,1806922 | accessdate = 2014-08-06 | newspaper = Ottawa Citizen | date = 1926-10-26}}</ref>。马尔霍尔对桑特尔有着很高的评价：
<blockquote>他是位了不起的导演，能够让人感到非常自然。他拥有像[[查理·卓别林|卓别林]]执导《[[巴黎一妇人|巴黎一妇人]]》（{{lang|en|''A Woman of Paris''}}）时那样的思路，在我看来，他与[[刘易斯·迈尔斯通|刘易斯·迈尔斯通]]和[[马尔科姆·圣克莱尔|马尔科姆·圣克莱尔]]（{{lang|en|Malcolm St. Clair}}）都给予他人相同的感触，都是新一代的导演。他们并不总是把时间花在技术问题上，把演员像木偶一样摆弄。<ref name="Inez">{{cite web | last1 = Sebastian | first1 = Inez | title = Discovered – Jack Mulhall | url = http://archive.org/stream/pictureplaymagaz25unse#page/n199/mode/2up | website = Picture-Play Magazine | publisher = [[互联网档案馆|Internet Archive]] | accessdate = 2014-08-06 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20151219160111/http://archive.org/stream/pictureplaymagaz25unse#page/n199/mode/2up | archive-date = 2015-12-19 | dead-url = no }}</ref></blockquote>

获选扮演女主角莎蒂·赫尔曼的多萝西·玛卡伊尔认为，这部电影能够吸引“美国的每个女孩”前来观看。她相信，“这部电影中的每个情节都有可能发生在任何一个女孩身上。这正是我所喜欢的。这里面没有任何一件事情不可能是真的。”<ref>{{cite news | title = "'Subway Sadie' A Film Story of Every Girl,"  Says Star. | newspaper = Lockport Union-Sun & Journal | date = 1927-01-18 | page = 2}}</ref>。其他演员和角色包括：查尔斯·默里（{{lang|en|Charles Murray}}）诠释[[司机|司机]]、佩吉·肖（{{lang|en|Peggy Shaw}}）出演埃塞尔（{{lang|en|Ethel}}）、加斯顿·格拉斯（{{lang|en|Gaston Glass}}）饰演弗雷德·佩里（{{lang|en|Fred Perry}}）、伯纳德·兰德尔（{{lang|en|Bernard Randall}}）扮演布朗（{{lang|en|Brown}}）<ref name="se">{{cite web | title = Subway Sadie | url = http://www.silentera.com/PSFL/data/S/SubwaySadie1926.html | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140113022322/http://www.silentera.com/PSFL/data/S/SubwaySadie1926.html | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2014-01-13 | work = Silent Era | accessdate = 2014-08-06 }}</ref>。

亚瑟·艾德森是[[黑白|黑白]][[无声电影|无声片]]《地铁莎蒂》的摄影指导<ref name="se" />。影片在纽约[[中央公园_(纽约市)|中央公园]]附近的多个地点取景，其中包括克丽欧佩特拉方尖碑<ref name="Koszarski-2008">{{cite book | ref = harv | last = Koszarski | first = Richard | title = Hollywood On the Hudson: Film and Television in New York from Griffith to Sarnoff | url = http://books.google.com/books?id=EF2xmI5pEx8C&pg=PA129 | date = 2008-08-27 | publisher = Rutgers University Press | isbn = 978-0-8135-4552-3 | page = 129 | accessdate = 2014-08-06}}</ref>和当地一家[[赌场|赌场]][[客栈|客栈]]，这也是这里第一次成为电影的取景地<ref>{{cite news | title = Attractions at Showhouse Offer Variety | accessdate = 2014-08-06 | url = http://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=2206&dat=19261126&id=UkAuAAAAIBAJ&sjid=WNgFAAAAIBAJ&pg=6565,71316 | newspaper = The Miami News | date = 1926-11-26}}</ref>。片中还有一场[[夜总会|夜总会]]的戏也是在纽约取景拍摄<ref>{{cite news | title = Plaza | accessdate = 2014-08-06 | newspaper = St. Petersburg Times | url = http://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=888&dat=19260913&id=KxBPAAAAIBAJ&sjid=oUwDAAAAIBAJ&pg=5460,7294304 | date = 1926-09-13}}</ref>。休·贝内特担任电影的剪辑师，艾尔·罗克特制片厂负责制作<ref name="se" />。1926年6月，罗克特向《电影新闻》表示电影已经拍摄完成<ref>{{cite web | title = Pictures and People | url = http://archive.org/stream/motionpicture33moti#page/n1063/mode/2up | website = Motion Picture News | publisher = [[互联网档案馆|Internet Archive]] | access-date = 2014-08-06 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20131108002552/http://archive.org/stream/motionpicture33moti#page/n1063/mode/2up | archive-date = 2013-11-08 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。1926年8月18日，第一国家影业为影片发出了版权申请<ref name="afi" />。最终完成的作品有7卷长，胶片全长2050米<ref name="se" />，播放时长约为70分钟<ref>{{cite web | last = Erickson | first = Hal | title = Subway Sadie | url = http://www.nytimes.com/movies/movie/112151/Subway-Sadie/overview | work = [[纽约时报|The New York Times]] | publisher = The New York Times Company | accessdate = 2014-08-06 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140124075829/http://www.nytimes.com/movies/movie/112151/Subway-Sadie/overview | archivedate = 2014-01-24 }}</ref>。

== 发行和反响 ==
[[File:Subway_Sadie_film_still_Picture-Play_jpg_version.jpg|thumb]]
《地铁莎蒂》的发行通过第一国家影业进行，影片于1926年9月12日在纽约[[首演|首映]]<ref name="afi" />。电影获得了良好的评价，《[[纽约时报|纽约时报]]》的一位记者称这是“一部有趣的电影”。评价中认为电影的结局缺乏惊喜，但就全片来说仍然让人赏心悦目<ref>{{cite news | title = A Subway Guard's Romance | archivedate = 2014-01-24 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140124075831/http://www.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9900E2D9163CEE3ABC4B52DFBF66838D639EDE | url = http://www.nytimes.com/movie/review?res=9900E2D9163CEE3ABC4B52DFBF66838D639EDE | accessdate = 2014-08-06 | newspaper = [[纽约时报|The New York Times]] | date = 1926-09-13 | deadurl = no }}</ref>。《独立晚报》（{{lang|en|''The Evening Independent''}}）也称赞了这部电影，赞扬这是“这个季度最巧妙、最有趣的电影之一”<ref>{{cite news | title = Herbert Clifton is Star on Keith Bill This Week | accessdate = 2014-08-06 | newspaper = Evening Independent | date = 1926-12-10 | url = http://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=950&dat=19261210&id=re9PAAAAIBAJ&sjid=t1QDAAAAIBAJ&pg=3410,1909719}}</ref>。

《电影剧》（{{lang|en|''Photoplay''}}）杂志的一篇评论称赞了玛卡伊尔的表演，形容这部电影讲述了“一个真实与人性的故事”<ref>{{cite web | title = Photoplay | url = https://archive.org/stream/photoplay3133movi/photoplay3133movi_djvu.txt | work = Photoplay | publisher = [[互联网档案馆|Internet Archive]] | accessdate = 2014-08-06 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140413155846/http://archive.org/stream/photoplay3133movi/photoplay3133movi_djvu.txt | archive-date = 2014-04-13 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。《电影先驱报》（{{lang|en|''Motion Picture Herald''}}）的评论中则认为影片没有什么特别值得称道之处，但仍然是一部值得欣赏的佳作，文章中还称赞了马尔霍尔的表演<ref>{{cite web | title = Exhibitors Herald and Moving Picture World | url = http://archive.org/stream/exhibitorsherald91unse/exhibitorsherald91unse_djvu.txt | work = Moving Picture Herald | publisher = [[互联网档案馆|Internet Archive]] | accessdate = 2014-08-06 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160316175843/http://archive.org/stream/exhibitorsherald91unse/exhibitorsherald91unse_djvu.txt | archive-date = 2016-03-16 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。《伯克利每日公报》（{{lang|en|''Berkeley Daily Gazette''}}）的一篇文章称赞了电影的剧情、导演技巧和表演，称其已达到少见的辉煌高度<ref>{{cite news | title = Subway Sadie To be Exhibited Here | url = http://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1970&dat=19261211&id=LDEiAAAAIBAJ&sjid=pKYFAAAAIBAJ&pg=3055,6060445 | accessdate = 2014-08-06 | newspaper = Berkeley Daily Gazette | date = 1926-12-11}}</ref>。

《早间电讯报》（{{lang|en|''The Morning Telegraph''}}）在评论中称，《地铁莎蒂》会让“大部分站在车上的乘客感到满意”，并且相信电影会有“极佳的[[票房|票房]]成绩”。《[[纽约新闻报|纽约新闻报]]》也给出正面评价，称这是一部“充满魅力的轻喜剧”。《[[纽约世界报|纽约世界报]]》（{{lang|en|''New York World''}}）的评论称电影讲了个“始终如一、似模像样的故事”，还称赞了桑特尔的导演技巧<ref name="reviews">{{cite web | title = Subway Sadie advert | accessdate = 2014-08-06 | url = http://archive.org/stream/filmdaily3738newy#page/728/mode/2up | work = The Film Daily | publisher = [[互联网档案馆|Internet Archive]] | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140808045811/http://www.archive.org/stream/filmdaily3738newy#page/728/mode/2up | archive-date = 2014-08-08 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。《[[每日镜报|每日镜报]]》的一篇评论赞赏了玛卡伊尔的表演和桑特尔的导演能力<ref name="reviews" />，《阅读鹰报》（{{lang|en|''Reading Eagle''}}）也称赞了两位主角的表演，称他们是“恒星般（亮眼）的组合”<ref>{{cite news | newspaper = Reading Eagle | date = 1926-10-24 | title = Dorothy Mackaill in Subway Sadie | url = http://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1955&dat=19261024&id=icMhAAAAIBAJ&sjid=aZ0FAAAAIBAJ&pg=3278,5112765 | accessdate = 2014-08-06}}</ref>。不过，影片也并非没有负面评价，《教育银幕》（{{lang|en|''The Educational Screen''}}）的评论中就认为这部电影中的内容都是些老生常谈<ref>{{cite web | title = Subway Sadie | url = http://www.archive.org/stream/educationalscree05chicrich#page/610/mode/2up | work = The Educational Screen | publisher = [[互联网档案馆|Internet Archive]] | accessdate = 2014-08-06 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20140113014113/http://www.archive.org/stream/educationalscree05chicrich#page/610/mode/2up | archive-date = 2014-01-13 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

1927年6月，《[[东南密苏里人报|东南密苏里人报]]》（{{lang|en|''Southeast Missourian''}}）的一位记者发文称，《地铁莎蒂》已经成为一部“非常成功”的电影<ref>{{cite news | title = Ball Game Played by Artificial Light Is Dazzling Success | url = http://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=1893&dat=19270625&id=5IQoAAAAIBAJ&sjid=DtQEAAAAIBAJ&pg=4004,2023301 | accessdate = 2014-08-06 | newspaper = The Southeast Missourian | date = 1927-06-25}}</ref>。马尔霍尔和玛卡伊尔的银幕组合广受好评，有评价称他们“真是个完美组合”，希望他们能在将来的多部电影中再度合作<ref name="Inez" />。两人在《地铁莎蒂》后还合作出演了1927年的《笑吧兄弟，微笑》（{{lang|en|''Smile, Brother, Smile''}}）<ref>{{cite web | title = Smile, Brother, Smile | url = http://www.tcm.com/tcmdb/title/499516/Smile-Brother-Smile/ | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140806102625/http://www.tcm.com/tcmdb/title/499516/Smile-Brother-Smile/ | archivedate = 2014-08-06 | website = Turner Classic Movies | accessdate = 2014-08-06 }}</ref>、1928年的《土耳其浴室的女士之夜》（{{lang|en|''Ladies' Night in a Turkish Bath''}}）<ref>{{cite web | last1 = Erickson | first1 = Hal | title = Ladies' Night in a Turkish Bath | url = http://www.allmovie.com/movie/ladies-night-in-a-turkish-bath-v98444 | website = [[AllRovi|Allmovie]] | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140806102904/http://www.allmovie.com/movie/ladies-night-in-a-turkish-bath-v98444 | deadurl = no | accessdate = 2014-08-06 | archivedate = 2014-08-06 }}</ref>和《端庄淑女》（{{lang|en|''Lady Be Good''}}）<ref>{{cite web | title = Lady Be Good | url = http://www.afi.com/members/catalog/DetailView.aspx?s=1&Movie=10127 | website = [[美国影艺协会|American Film Institute]] | accessdate = 2014-08-06 | archivedate = 2014-04-17 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140417023612/http://www.afi.com/members/catalog/DetailView.aspx?s=1&Movie=10127 }}</ref>，以及1929年的《丽兹的孩子》（{{lang|en|''Children of the Ritz''}}）<ref>{{cite web | last1 = Erickson | first1 = Hal | title = Children of the Ritz | url = http://www.allmovie.com/movie/children-of-the-ritz-v87181 | website = [[AllRovi|Allmovie]] | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140806103403/http://www.allmovie.com/movie/children-of-the-ritz-v87181 | deadurl = no | archivedate = 2014-08-06 | accessdate = 2014-08-06 }}</ref>；1933年的《八点钟的帷幕》（{{lang|en|''Curtain at Eight''}}）是两人的最后一次合作<ref name="Pitts-1997">{{cite book | last = Pitts | first = Michael R. | title = Poverty row studios, 1929–1940: an illustrated history of 53 independent film companies, with a filmography for each | page = 224 | url = http://books.google.com/books?id=hGpZAAAAMAAJ | year = 1997 | publisher = McFarland & Co. | accessdate = 2014-08-06 | isbn = 978-0-7864-0168-0}}</ref>。

《地铁莎蒂》的放映一直持续到了1928年1月12日<ref>{{cite news | title = Euclid | accessdate = 2014-08-06 | url = http://news.google.com/newspapers?nid=888&dat=19280112&id=Hl1PAAAAIBAJ&sjid=ck4DAAAAIBAJ&pg=5959,2567832 | newspaper = The St. Petersburg Times | date = 1928-01-12}}</ref>，但是截至2007年11月，这部电影的拷贝已无法确定是否尚存，影片很可能已经佚失<ref name="se" />，只有[[纽约运输博物馆|纽约运输博物馆]]还保存有本片的一张[[海报|海报]]<ref>{{cite web | last1 = Plitt | first1 = Amy | title = Highlights of the New York Transit Museum in New York City | url = http://www.timeout.com/newyork/museums/ten-must-sees-at-the-new-york-transit-museum-cultural-center?pageNumber=2 | website = [[Time_Out|Time Out]] | accessdate = 2014-08-06 | archivedate = 2014-07-26 | deadurl = no | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20140726203601/http://www.timeout.com/newyork/museums/ten-must-sees-at-the-new-york-transit-museum-cultural-center?pageNumber=2 }}</ref>。

